## Phase one: The description and attachment

On first look, the animation in the picture looked familiar, like a game‚Äôs. I proceeded by **reverse searching the image on google lens and got this:**

**Yep, it is indeed a game, Dark Souls 3.**¬†

   This is a game that my roommates really adore and have played a lot so i knew a bunch of references in the title and the description.


   For example, the title **‚ÄúEchoes of the abyss‚Äù**. And i knew of the existence of something called the ‚Äú**firelink**‚Äù in the game already, so the **‚Äúlink to the fire‚Äù** was a giveaway too as there is a place in the game called as **Firelink Shrine**.¬†


   Now that this is a OSINT challenge in a CTF, no way the image would've been given just for us to understand the reference. **There is definitely a possibility something is hidden in the image too.**



**Let's look closer in the image.**

   I use **Exiftool** to look at the image metadata:

	 **"In the final primes of 100,.there lies the last flame that turns the log to ash. .Its echo lingers where the blue bird once sang."**

	 last cinder is indeed a dark souls reference, so that part of the clue is definiely **Lastcinder**

   ![[Pasted image 20251225231105.png]]
   

   ==Now here's a tip for you if you encounter github repositories in your future OSINT challenges===
	- Dont go straight into the source codes to find the flag
	- first, look at other things like:
		- issues
		- pull requests
		- tags
		- forks
		- commit history
		- collaborators and contributers
	- then read the README thoroughly
	- only after this you should go to the source code, if necessary
 **Trust me you will save a lot of time this way**
